        Just another 20 days until Halloween folks. I know how excited you are, and you just know I'm in it for the money as well. Then again, all you need to do to upset the public at large these days is to hold a war-torn nation's flag. I can assure you the vitriol will be legendary. Anyways, the chart is as (eclectic/stale/awful/insert any adjective you want) as ever, and not just because Coldplay released an album that was bought by WAY TOO MANY PEOPLE. 237K is just a "little" too far for an album that couldn't be more middle-of-the-road and/or bandwagon-jumping if it had duetted with Charli XCX. More on her next week.

        Elsewhere, Sabrina will never leave our braincells, the likes of Public Service Broadcasting, Jake Bugg, Alison Moyet, The Smile, and James Bay realise that releasing new albums on the same day as Chris 'Industry Plant' Martin is a very bad idea, Gigi Perez is now officially noticed by the masses and it's caused your usual furore, and KSI makes his grand return with the kind of song backlash that makes it looks like he just announced he wants to FR3E P4LE5T1NE or whatever. Not that sampling a forgotten hit from the Red Hot Chili Peppers was a bad idea, it's just that he probably shouldn't have hired Trippie Redd to hang out with him on it. Not like anyone can tell though. Even I'm having trouble wondering why he didn't just steal the chorus like a normal person would. Maybe he'd get less opprobrium (harsh criticism).

        Oh, and the latest Netflix-related incident to buzzsaw the Top 40 in half is Monsters: The Lyle and Erik Menendez Story, a tale of two people 'annihilating' their mothers from 1989, and it's suddenly resulted in Don't Dream It's Over by Aussie-crooners Crowded House, and Girl I'm Gonna Miss You by the (not real) vocal talents of Milli Vanilli to chart again. Don't ask, OK? You can't go one month in the charts nowadays without some old track gaining a second wind. Anyways, more noodlings from me in seven days time. Because I have better things to do then talk about cassö for the millionth time without gritting my teeth.
